caption: The Red Feather was one of the first high end restaurants on 8th St. It maintains a high standard.  Expect to spend some cash.... **Sadly a victim of the downtown shutdown, Red Feather has closed**

We decided to splurge and try the cast iron rib eye. OH MY. One of the best steaks I have ever had. The cut and cook was perfect and the demi glace complimented the meat without overtaking the flavor. We absolutely love this restaurant but the rib eye was a super special treat for sure!

The food that we had was incredible, and the drinks were excellent. Our waitress Rebecca was completely awesome - she was very friendly, had good recommendations of food and drink, and checked back several times to make sure we were enjoying the experience. When we go back (and we will be back), I hope that we will be served by her again.

Our waitress Rebecca was completely awesome - she was very friendly, had good recommendations of food and drink, and checked back several times to make sure we were enjoying the experience. When we go back (and we will be back), I hope that we will be served by her again. I highly recommend anyone in Boise to come to the Red Feather Lounge!
Such a classy place with amazing drinks and meals. The kale salad was to die for and that’s a hard one to make delicious!

Yum!! We were in Boise for the Idaho potato bowl, so glad we went here!! For entrees, my dad and I got the spicy GOAT and the flying pig, both which were excellent. The flying pig was like a bbq pork pizza. The spicy goat was medium spice to me, but I love spicy food.
Spicy Brussel sprouts, oh and everything else is awesome. Very classy.

Delicious food and great craft cocktails. Must make a reservation on weekends for sure or you won’t get a table. Some portion sizes can be a bit small, so order a few things and share. Love this place and will be back!
Drink specials are great and the bartenders and some of the best in town. Sharing the space with bitter creek ale house, you can't really go wrong in 8th street. Would recommend for drinks and food

Love the atmosphere. Inventive cocktails (I love the literary names) and menu of fresh and, mostly, local food. Very friendly staff that pays just the right amount of attention.

Always a lovely experience. I feel classy and special thanks to the waiters and cooks. The quality of food is phenomenal, and I'm always excited to try their new items
Wonderful brunch options (including a kids menu)! We appreciated the staff accommodating our group on a busy morning.
Brunch was amazing. I love their breakfast menu Big fan and the staff is excellent.
The 3 things I enjoy best about Red Feather. The cocktails, the kale salad, the French fries w/homemade ketchup. Oh, and one more... The booth upstairs.
Incredible brunch. Fabulous coffee and spectacular food. Must have patience because service is a little slow but it's worth it.

The ambiance, welcoming hostess, knowledgeable and friendly waitstaff plus delicious food, makes the Red Feather Lounge the perfect place for a date, friends gathering or just because you want a delicious meal with all the bells and whistles. Highly recommended.
The scallops were perfectly cooked, and paired with Italian sausage was surprisingly light. The drinks were missed quickly and with enthusiasm, and tasted delicious.
Great atmosphere, good food.

Our waiter (Johny) made the night. The drinks were so good. Thanks for an amazing night. Steak was awesome as well!

Went for brunch. Long wait, but we grabbed a seat at the bar. Honestly, the awesome bartender and delicious Apple Cider Mimosa and Bloody Mary she made the brunch experience. The drinks were delicious and we started the beignets were equally yum! Warm and slightly crunchy outside and rich and soft inside with a delicious dipping sauce. The entrees were mediocre, the Eggs Benedict and the Skillet. I’d try it again, but for the price I expected the food to be a little more then ok.

BEST drinks in Boise. Go sit at the bar, order some drinks, people watch, talk to the bartenders, watch the weird things on the TV, order some food. This place has the best vibe in Boise. Upscale, but not arrogant. The bartenders make a fabulous drink selection of things you've never tried before--which seem  to be changed out seasonally. Each one is perfect, and beautiful, in it's own way. If you want something more intimate, head upstairs. If you're planning on dinner, make a reservation! (Don't forget to try the fries...Seriously! And stay for the dessert.) Plan to pay for the quality, it's worth it. (Shout out to Daniel and Chris--so nice, and made us feel like we belonged.)
Food was spectacular and our server Rocked it!!!! Johnny is awesome...:)
Always a go-to place for good cocktails and dessert!

It's too bad 6 stars isn't a thing. The food is superb, bested only by the service and friendliness of the staff! I recommend it to people often because I know that they will not be let down. I can't wait to go back!

Food was great but service was slow. Not necessarily the servers fault he was the only one there, but if you have an hour lunch you may be running late. We ordered right after sitting down and it took about 50 minutes to get our food.

Came for brunch, and our reservation was ready on time. I think we either hit an off or busy morning though, because even though we got seated, we weren't served right away, and several times found ourselves waiting for someone to come back and check up and/or take our order.  The food was amazing though, and I highly recommend the cheddar potato side (far superior to the crispy). There were also an impressive number of options for our vegetarian members. However, we ordered bingets, and then didn't get them until after the meal, when we reminded the waiter. But, they were on the house as an apology. Would definitely come back!

The waiter didn’t realize I didn’t get anything so we had to wait for him to comeback so that we could tell him I never got my order. The appetizers were very good, I was very impressed by each one we got. There were 5 we got so I don’t remember the names. Very pretty restaurant and the private upstairs area was very nice. Great brunch too, and one of my favorite spots in Boise for a bite and drink.

Red Feather is perfect for a date. It has low lighting and a beautiful display of wines. They also have a wide selection of local and cellared beers. All of their food is farm to table. I would HIGHLY suggest ordering the brussel sprouts as an appetizer.

I have been here before. Really great place to relax have some great drinks and amazing food. Was a little saddened to have my salmon be just a little overcooked. Was a little tough to eat but overall The Experience wait staff and food was great. I will be going back next time I'm in Boise.
Great food and wonderful service. Tight seating was the only concern. But otherwise worth the price and a must go.

We stopped in for a light dinner back in February when we were in town. The restaurant is very gay-friendly. Our server was a nice gentleman named Alex. We found out that it was the end of Tiki Week. We tried some fun Polynesian cocktails. One was called Port light, and the other one was called "I don't know how to pronounce that." Both were very tasty, and decorated festively with fresh orchids. We split an appetizer made of thinly sliced potatoes, and a pizza. Both were great! I would love to go back and have more of a traditional dinner sometime.
A little much, but it was nice
Go have this burger. Rosemary marrow butter, for the love of God. And a spot-on Vieux Carre further away from New Orleans than I had supposed was likely, but is.

Chill on the patio and watch people on the street.  Prohibition era cocktails and to die for begnets.

The environment is pleasant, if a bit cramped.  The service was top-notch, folks were very pleasant and attentive.  Would especially like to compliment our waitress, Beverly.  This is not the first time I've encountered her there, and she's been a joy each time.  She and the management went out of their way to make our experience enjoyable.  I tried a couple of their mixed drinks, one traditional and one an experimental.  Both were very tasty, but the experimental one in particular was a huge ice cube with only a few swallows of drink.  I enjoyed them, but especially for the money the value was not there.  This theme carried over into my entree, the scallops.  They were delicious, but there were only three scallops presented on the plate, and it was one of the most expensive items on the menu.  I understand if that's what it costs for the meal, but I would recommend that the menu clearly reflect that it's a tiny dish (smaller than most appetizers).  Perhaps they could price it as "small plate" and "large plate", for more money...I see that often with cuts of prime rib, for instance.  For dessert we had the beignets with butterscotch dip, which were fabulous and perfect size to share.  Overall an excellent experience, with the caveat that if you're hungry, an appetizer is well-advised.

My wife and I had a date night planned and decided to try Red Feather for dinner.  It is a bit more of a lounge than we expected but we were seated upstairs and it was OUTSTANDING!  Very relaxed, quiet and away from any type of hustle and bustle.  Our waiter, Will, was absolutely flawless.  Will was very attentive, experienced and didn't hover.  We will certainly be back!!
Love the quality of the food and drinks, great staff, great location.
Love, LOVE the late night happy hour. Their amazing poutine was life changing at the end of a fun night. Raved about it for days.

First time my wife and I had been there.  Almost everything was awesome. The ONE minor issue I had, is it was loud. People talking, and music made it difficult for me to understand my wife. I don't have the best hearing... My wife didn't have a problem understanding me.  So, that was the one minor negative. The rest was amazing.  They were very busy, yet the staff were super friendly and terrific.  The drinks. My wife and I sampled 4 of their drinks. 2 from their experimental group and 2 from the more normal groups. Well mixed. Great tasting. Top notch work on the drinks.  Now, for the food.  We had a special deal that gave us an appetizer, salad, entree and a shared desert.  It was all pretty much a step or two beyond any expectations I had. The chips of the appetizer were sliced and cooked to perfection. Seriously, how can they keep that level of consistency with the amount of food in the appetizer?  Next were salads. My wife got the beet salad.  She liked it, but preferred mine, as did I. It was a cooked salad with a delecious dressing and cooked croutons and cheese. Seriously, best salad I have had.  Next dinner. The NY Strip was cooked perfect. The fingerling potatoes were too. All delicious. I was pretty much tapped out at half the steak and 2 small potatoes. You get a lot. My wife got the trout. Again, cooked to perfection. Delicious.  Desert. I really have no clue what these were. We waited a bit for them to be srrved. It let my stomach settle. It was kind of a puff all thing with a caramel dipping sauce. Decadent. Delicious. Yea, you get the idea. Another supurb dish.  We will be back, and hopefully sooner rather than later. My wife and I were blown away by the perfection of the dishes, the exquisitely mixed and presented drinks, and the amazing service.
Food and drinks are always good here.

Great food great atmosphere highly recommend! FYI they have a upper level for additional dining. When you first come in you may not notice Aloft area but if you had around towards the wine rack with a spiral staircase there's another staircase to your right that goes upstairs.
The food was delicious and the service impeccable (Brody amazing!)! I'd go back just to sit at this gentleman's section!

Had an amazing time here! The food was unbelievable! From the pepper appetizer to the fig salad then on to the New York strip, all of it was just delicious. The beer selection was also excellent. So many options, truly awesome. There service was also on par. Can't wait to go back.

Had a wonderful time at the bar, was lucky to be there during Tiki week! The drinks were great (as was the bartender), and having James Bond playing in the background was a bonus!

Enjoyed a great brunch today! First time at Red Feather and glad I finally made a point to try it. Service was friendly and fast and the restaurant has a cozy vibe even though it is two stories and quite roomy. I had eggs Benedict and a waffle both of which were tasty. Lots of great and yummy choices on the menu. My husband had one of the skillet scrambles and our friend had chicken and biscuits which also tasted great.

Urban chic place is great for a beverage (good local brews + wines) and appetizer before a show or a good place for dinner. Halibut Tacos a big hit with this couple. First time there but will be going back for sure when it's warmer and sit on the patio!

Our waiter, I can't recall his name. Blonde skinny fella, he was amazing. He made our whole experience. Of course the ambiance is lovely and Brussels sprouts are killer! This guy really left a spot on our heart.  After we had left we got a phone call from the resturant to let us know we had forgotten a device of ours there. Very nice.  I really felt like everyone here did everything they could to make us feel welcome. And I could talk about dessert all night, some sort of New Orleans donut?? Something alone those lines.  Please try this place out! They,are doing great things!!
Great appetizers and drinks! Big fan of there Beignets with butterscotch. Delicious!

Came for a friend’s birthday dinner. It was a busy evening and the front of house took a bit to identify the party we were with.  We ordered the Glazed Pork Belly appetizer. Being Korean, I recognized that it was supposed to be a spin on two traditional korean dishes. The pancake (pajeon in Korean) wasn’t cooked thru making the middle taste of nothing but pancake batter. Additionally, the kurabota pork belly was drowning in the glaze and the sriracha crema totally eliminating the savory flavor of that piece of pork. Appetizer - completely unimpressed. The meal redeemed the dining. We ordered the pizza featuring the pork belly and that was extremely well done.  Overall, I would come back to Red Feather but would steer away from the Korean “inspired” appetizer.

Food was pretty good. The setting was strange though, and the menu felt limited especially in terms of non alcoholic drinks. It was good until the waitress took my food before I was done! I had like 1/3 of my food left and she just grabbed it without asking. Then we waited a long time for the check. Definitely only for a certain kind of people, an acquired taste.

Have never had a "great" experience here...just somewhere between OK & pretty good.  Unfortunately had a bad experience at Red Feather recently.  Arrived at 11:30 am for a business meeting.  My client arrived at 11:45.  Service was a bit slow to start but got worse.  Waiter took our order at noon & returned about 35 minutes later saying our order had been lost.  He took it again, said they'd rush it, & it'd be on the house.  Very nice offer but by 1 pm, no food!  I'd been there 90 minutes & had to go.  Stuff happens, of course, but Red Feather just hasn't impressed the 5-6 times I've been there.  In a nutshell:  good food; friendly but slow service; cramped space; priced on the high side.  Overall value - meh.

Excellent! Unique menu. Couscous risotto was AMAZING. This place has majority of their food locally sourced from ethical and decently sustainable farmers. They even compost! My server Body (bodie?) was fun and personable each time I’ve had him! Love red feather! Try the housemade ketchup.
